						<summary>

						<p>On the tiers of the entrance to the Saṅgamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Dated Śaka [1149], <hi rend="italic">Chaitra</hi> śu. 7, Thursday, corresponding to A.D. 1227, March 25. The cyclic year is Sarvajit. [The Govt. Epigraphist could not trace the Śaka year on the stone, but NDI, Part II, No. 102 refers to the Śaka year. By the time of the visit of the Epigraphical officer, the stone could have peeled off.]</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record some gift by Bhaima • • la-sāni for the merit of her husband.</p>						

						</summary>
